snippet.title: Both Indiana children located after Amber Alert found dead in mother’s car
snippet.description:
FT. WAYNE, Ind. (WKRC) - An AMBER Alert was cancelled for two children in Fort Wayne, Indiana. 

Local 12 News has learned that both 7-year-old Lilian Hernandez and 6-year-old Rene Pasztor were found dead in the backseat of their mother's car. 

Local 12's sister station, WSBT, reported an officer was stopped outside the police department around 5:30 p.m. Monday, September 26, by the children's biological mother, Amber Pasztor. She told the officer there were two dead children in the back seat of the car. 

Deputies believed the children were in  extreme danger after being abducted by Pasztor Monday morning. She did not have custody.



The following release was issued by the Elkhart Police Department Monday night, September 26:

On Monday September 26, 2016 at 12:51 PM the Allen County Sheriff’s Department issued an Amber Alert with regards to two missing children, which they believed to be in danger. At the time of the Amber Alert, it was believed the children were abducted by their mother.

On Monday September 26, 2016 at 5:25 PM an officer who was walking out of the Elkhart Police Department, on Marion Street, was stopped by a subject driving a vehicle. The subject driving the vehicle reported to the officer there were two (2) deceased subjects inside the vehicle. Upon examining the vehicle officers located two deceased juveniles in the backseat of the vehicle.

Upon further investigation officers discovered the vehicle the subject was driving matched the vehicle information provided in the Amber Alert; a gold Mercury.

The female driver of the vehicle has been identified as Amber Pasztor. Further investigation is underway to better understand the circumstances surrounding the children’s death.

At this time the two juveniles located inside the vehicle are believed to be Liliana Hernandez and Rene Pasztor. However formal identification of the two juveniles will be done by the Coroner’s Office at a later time.

We are currently looking trying to determine the whereabouts of one Frank Macomber who may have additional information.

At this point in the investigation detectives from the Elkhart Police Department Homicide Unit are working with detectives from the Allen County Sheriff’s Department Homicide unit.

The following release was issued earlier in the day:

The Allen County Sheriff is investigating the abduction of two children from Fort Wayne, Indiana.

Liliana Hernandez is a 7-year-old white female, 3 ft, 4 in tall, long brown hair, brown eyes and was last seen wearing a black nightgown.

Rene Pasztor is a 6-year-old white male, 3 ft tall, short brown hair, brown eyes and was last seen wearing black shorts.

The children were last seen at 6:21 am EDT in Fort Wayne, IN and are believed to be in extreme danger.

Fort Wayne, Indiana is 125 miles north of Indianapolis, Indiana.

Allen County Sheriff believes the children were likely abducted by their non-custodial mother Amber Pasztor a 29-year-old white female, 5 ft, 6 in tall, 250 lbs., with long blonde hair. Suspect vehicle is a Mercury, Mystique, Tan in color.

If you have any information on these children, contact the Allen County Sheriff at 260-449-7661.
